Cook noodles in boiling water 6 minutes; drain. Combine soy sauce, vinegar, sugar, oil, and crushed red pepper, stirring well with a whisk. Heat a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Coat pan with cooking spray. Add bell pepper strips; saute 2 minutes. Add bok choy; saute 1 minute. Add tofu and garlic; saute 2 minutes. Add noodles and soy sauce mixture; cook 2 minutes or until thoroughly heated, tossing well to coat. Sprinkle with onions and cilantro.